The paper deals with virus spreading dynamics in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The modified SI epidemic model proposed in the paper incorporates spatial correlation, node density, sensing range, transmission range, and total sensor nodes, which are all parameters related to network topology and structure. Therefore, the paper could also be categorized under cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.CR (cryptography and security). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which could fall under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.IT (information theory).
